Ganita
Hora
Samhita
Prasna
Shakuna

The mathematics of astrology is Ganita or siddhanta.

Siddhantas are used in the preparation of mathematical tables, the almanacs or the panchang.

Samhita (mundane astrology)deals with the planetary effects on nature and collective issues of mankind. Things like rains, weather, epidemics, floods.

Hora (Individual astrology) is the most popular branch of astrology, it deals with predictions about individuals, their happiness and unhappiness, achievements and failures, hopes and despairs and every other facet of life.

Prasna (Horary astrology) is specially useful for people who do not have horoscopes I.e., time of birth and place of birth information is unavailable. 

Prasna astrology is based on charts drawn at the time of communication of questioner to the astrologer.

Some predictions are made using kerala's Anga shastra where the enquirer touching any part of his body or naming of random flower and the way of  answering questions asked by the astrologer are taken as cues to design birth chart.

Shakuna astrology is not directly based on planetary movements, predictions are made based on Omens.

